# Enler — Next.js Coding Standards

## Project Context
The Next.js app (`enler_web/`) serves two purposes:
1. **Public quiz player** — Friends visit a shared link to play a quiz in the browser.
2. **Share card landing page** — Beautiful OG image / result page for social sharing.

It is NOT a full replica of the Flutter app. Keep it focused and lightweight.

## App Router Structure

```
src/app/
├── [locale]/                    # Dynamic locale segment (tr for v1)
│   ├── layout.tsx               # Locale-aware layout with providers
│   ├── page.tsx                 # Landing / marketing page
│   ├── quiz/
│   │   └── [id]/
│   │       ├── page.tsx         # Quiz play page (Server Component shell)
│   │       └── quiz-player.tsx  # Client Component (interactive quiz)
│   └── result/
│       └── [id]/
│           └── page.tsx         # Result + share card page
├── api/                         # API routes (if needed beyond Supabase)
│   └── og/
│       └── route.tsx            # OG image generation
├── layout.tsx                   # Root layout (html, body, fonts)
├── globals.css                  # Global styles + CSS custom properties
├── not-found.tsx                # 404 page
└── error.tsx                    # Error boundary
```

## Server vs Client Components

### Default: Server Components
Every component is a Server Component unless it needs interactivity.

```tsx
// ✅ Server Component (default) — no directive needed
export default async function QuizPage({ params }: Props) {
  const quiz = await getQuiz(params.id);
  return <QuizShell quiz={quiz} />;
}
```

### When to use `'use client'`
Add `'use client'` ONLY when the component:
- Uses React hooks (`useState`, `useEffect`, `useRef`, etc.)
- Uses browser APIs (`window`, `document`, `localStorage`)
- Handles user events (`onClick`, `onChange`, `onSubmit`)
- Uses context providers
- Needs Realtime subscriptions

```tsx
'use client';

import { useState } from 'react';

export function QuizPlayer({ questions }: Props) {
  const [currentIndex, setCurrentIndex] = useState(0);
  // Interactive quiz logic...
}
```

### Rules
- Keep `'use client'` boundary as low as possible in the component tree.
- Pass serializable data from Server → Client components via props.
- Never import server-only code (db, secrets) in client components.
- Use `next/dynamic` for heavy client components:
  ```tsx
  const QuizPlayer = dynamic(() => import('./quiz-player'), {
    loading: () => <QuizSkeleton />,
  });
  ```

## TypeScript Standards

### Type Definitions
```tsx
// src/lib/types.ts — shared types
export interface Quiz {
  id: string;
  ownerUsername: string;
  questions: Question[];
  createdAt: string;
}

export interface Question {
  id: string;
  categorySlug: string;
  questionText: string;
  choices: Choice[];
}

export interface Choice {
  id: string;
  text: string;
  isCorrect: boolean;
}
```

### Rules
- Use `interface` for object shapes, `type` for unions/intersections.
- No `any` — use `unknown` and narrow with type guards.
- Strict mode enabled (`"strict": true` in tsconfig).
- Export types from `src/lib/types.ts` for shared use.
- Component props are defined as interfaces named `{Component}Props`.

## Supabase Client

### Server-Side (Server Components, Route Handlers)
```tsx
// src/lib/supabase/server.ts
import { createServerClient } from '@supabase/ssr';
import { cookies } from 'next/headers';

export async function createSupabaseServer() {
  const cookieStore = await cookies();
  return createServerClient(
    process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL!,
    process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY!,
    {
      cookies: {
        getAll: () => cookieStore.getAll(),
        setAll: (cookiesToSet) => {
          cookiesToSet.forEach(({ name, value, options }) =>
            cookieStore.set(name, value, options)
          );
        },
      },
    }
  );
}
```

### Client-Side (Client Components)
```tsx
// src/lib/supabase/client.ts
import { createBrowserClient } from '@supabase/ssr';

export function createSupabaseBrowser() {
  return createBrowserClient(
    process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL!,
    process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY!
  );
}
```

### Query Rules
```tsx
// ✅ Specific columns
const { data } = await supabase
  .from('quizzes')
  .select('id, owner_username, question_count, created_at')
  .eq('id', quizId)
  .maybeSingle();

// ❌ Never select all
const { data } = await supabase.from('quizzes').select('*');
```

## Localization (next-intl)

### Setup
```
src/messages/
└── tr.json          # Turkish messages (v1 only)
```

### Message File Structure
```json
{
  "common": {
    "loading": "Yükleniyor...",
    "error": "Bir hata oluştu",
    "retry": "Tekrar dene"
  },
  "quiz": {
    "title": "Quiz Zamanı!",
    "question": "{current}/{total}. Soru",
    "timeLeft": "{seconds} saniye kaldı",
    "submit": "Cevabı Gönder"
  },
  "result": {
    "title": "Sonuçlar",
    "score": "{score}/{total} doğru",
    "share": "Paylaş"
  }
}
```

### Usage in Server Components
```tsx
import { getTranslations } from 'next-intl/server';

export default async function QuizPage() {
  const t = await getTranslations('quiz');
  return <h1>{t('title')}</h1>;
}
```

### Usage in Client Components
```tsx
'use client';
import { useTranslations } from 'next-intl';

export function QuizTimer({ seconds }: Props) {
  const t = useTranslations('quiz');
  return <span>{t('timeLeft', { seconds })}</span>;
}
```

### Rules
- All UI strings through `next-intl`. Zero hardcoded Turkish text.
- Use namespaced keys: `common.`, `quiz.`, `result.`.
- Parameterized strings for dynamic content — never concatenate.
- Keep message keys in `camelCase`.

## Metadata & SEO

### Per-Page Metadata
```tsx
import type { Metadata } from 'next';

export async function generateMetadata({ params }: Props): Promise<Metadata> {
  const quiz = await getQuiz(params.id);
  return {
    title: `${quiz.ownerUsername} seni ne kadar tanıyor? | Enler`,
    description: 'Arkadaşının favorilerini tahmin et!',
    openGraph: {
      title: `${quiz.ownerUsername} - Enler Quiz`,
      description: 'Arkadaşının favorilerini tahmin et!',
      images: [`/api/og?quizId=${params.id}`],
      type: 'website',
    },
    twitter: {
      card: 'summary_large_image',
    },
  };
}
```

### Rules
- Every page MUST have `generateMetadata()`.
- OG images are generated dynamically via `/api/og/` route.
- Include `title`, `description`, and `openGraph` at minimum.
- Use Soft Aurora gradient in OG images (indigo → violet).

